other_tests.procedure_name: MRI of the Abdomen and Pelvis
other_tests.findings: Dilated, thickened distal appendix containing hyperintense material on T2-weighted imaging; appendix measured up to 11 mm in diameter; trace periappendiceal fluid; no abscess or perforation.
Acute suppurative appendicitis and periappendicitis; inflamed appendix with no signs of perforation identified during surgery.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Postoperative fetomaternal condition normal; incision healing well at follow-ups.
